data.description: *5.75%* assumable FHA mortage to qualified buyers.  Welcome to your new family home in the sought-after Grove Pointe Subdivision, which offers everything you need for a comfortable and convenient lifestyle! Situated in a community with a picturesque lake, double sidewalks, and charming street lighting, and top-ranked schools at every level in Sarasota.  Also, it's just a stone's throw from Doctors Hospital and the world-renowned powder sugar beaches of Siesta and Lido Key.  Outdoor enthusiasts will love the proximity to Nathan Benderson Park, where World Rowing Championships take place, as well as a host of other exciting outdoor activities. Convenience is key, with shopping, restaurants, golf courses and the Legacy Biking Trail all within easy reach. Step inside this former model home and be greeted by a family-friendly layout that features a split floor plan and vaulted ceilings.  The attention to detail is evident, with beautiful Norman Plantation shutters, stylish ceiling fans and energy-efficient LED lighting.  The heart of the home is the spacious kitchen, complete with a breakfast bar, eat-in space, closet pantry and reverse osmosis system for pure drinking water.  The separate laundry room with washer and dryer has built in cabinets and a deep sink.  The 2 car garage also has built in cabinets. The master suite is a true retreat, boasting a bonus room that can be used as an office, nursery or sitting room.  Open the sliding glass door and step onto the lanai, where you can relax and enjoy the Florida sunshine.  The master bedroom itself has been tastefully remodeled, featuring modern tile flooring and a custom-built walk-in closet.  The attached bathroom is a spa-like oasis, showcasing a travertine tile shower with dual shower heads, an inside bench and a sleek frameless shower door.  Double sinks with updated cabinetry, a stone counter and a separate tub complete the luxurious feel. Two additional spacious bedrooms have luxury vinyl flooring, offer ample closet space and share a full ceramic bathroom. The open floor plan seamlessly connects the dining room, with its new luxury vinyl flooring to the large ceramic tile great room.  Sliding glass doors lead to the lanai, which overlooks the expansive fenced-in backyard.  There's plenty of room here for family activities and even the possibility of adding a pool. Don't miss the opportunity to make this incredible property your own.  Call now for a private showing--the seller is motivated!
